				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Below is a guide you should follow when creating LLM tools for Glamorous Toolkit. Further learn more about the patterns for creating LLM tools  from related classes in the system."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:26.625447+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:28.217322+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "FIAsKnmySb69RqmhmC63rA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Follow the existing Magritte tool patterns for creating LLM tools. The tool must subclass {{gtClass:GtLAbstractMagritteFunctionTool}} and declare parameters via Magritte descriptions."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:34.102308+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:34.102308+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "d4ovL2jUQ9CSXt2mC+hTSA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Use domain objects to represent parameters and responses with Magritte descriptions and add {{gtPragma:gtView}} methods as needed. Include a JSON description for the tool’s responses in the tool’s `#description` method. Describe what the tool does and what parameters it expects."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:47.205294+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:52:29.518174+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "75lwl2M3TTW6cMGcpc1fSQ=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "- Subclass {{gtClass:GtLAbstractMagritteFunctionTool}}.\n- Implement:\n  - `#name` → tool name string (keep it identical to the old tool if migrating).\n  - `#description` → include JSON argument/response examples **matching Magritte serialization**.\n  - One Magritte description per input argument (e.g., `queryDescription`).\n  - `#privatePerformToolCall:inContext:` → implement the behavior and return a Magritte domain object.\n - Place the tool class in the package {{gtPackage:Gt4LlmCore}}"
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:55.885225+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:55.885225+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "Mkw2KsCfTMuvOSOYa9YWWg=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "#1) Create the tool class"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:51.912451+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T12:29:13.975323+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "+F+NuLv1TnaTshM5SiN8Ng=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "- Create a response domain object class (subclass Object) in {{gtPackage:Gt4LlmCore}}.\n- Use Magritte descriptions for all slots:\n  - `MAStringDescription` for strings.\n  - {{gtClass:MAToManyScalarRelationDescription}} for arrays of scalars.\n  - `MAToManyRelationDescription` for arrays of domain objects.\n- Add {{gtPragma:gtView}} methods for key collections.\n- Implement `printOn:` to summarize the object.\n\n**Tip:** Prefer reuse of existing domain objects (e.g., {{gtClass:GtLMethodsSearchResult}}) when semantics align.\n"
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:58.560035+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:50:58.560035+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "h66MF2WWTTG84MwaT3iTEw=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "## 2) Model the response explicitly"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:52:45.635422+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-06T11:52:45.635422+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "94L15zg4R02KkXqDGzq0Yw=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "When a response is derived from a list of matches, add a utility constructor (e.g., `fromMatches:` or `fromReferences:`) that:\n- **Normalizes the collection** with `asArray` before slicing.\n- Limits results (typically 200).\n- Sets `mayHaveMore`.\n\n**Template:**\n```smalltalk\nfromMatches: aCollection\n\t| matchesArray limited |\n\tmatchesArray := aCollection asArray.\n\tlimited := matchesArray first: (200 min: matchesArray size).\n\t^ self new\n\t\tfoundClassNames: (limited collect: #name);\n\t\tmayHaveMore: matchesArray size > 200;\n\t\tyourself\n```\n\nUse the constructor from the tool to keep logic in one place.\n"
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
